It is only a matter of time before Faith Dingle (Sally Dexter) loses her battle with terminal cancer in Emmerdale. She has a fractured relationship with her son Cain Dingle (Jeff Hordley) and he has never been able to forgive her for pretending she had died in a car crash. Will he learn to let go of the past before she dies in upcoming scenes? The drama unfolds when Faith's palliative care nurse tells her it is crucial to focus on dying without any regrets.Eric Pollard (Chris Chittell) later reassures Faith her bucket list is a good idea and the pair feel emotional about what lies ahead for the Emmerdale matriarch.When Faith struggles on a country walk with daughter Chas Dingle (Lucy Pargeter), she's saddened to see another painful reminder of her mum’s deteriorating health.However, Faith perks up when she sees a farmer nearby and flags him down to rescue them. READ MORE: Meghan Markle and Prince Harry coverage slammed by GMB viewers Later on, Chas is left stunned when Faith tells her she wants to hold a party before it is too late.They start planning a farewell party for the Emmerdale stalwart but Cain feels uneasy about attending.He's reluctant to attend for fear of how upsetting he'll find it and is left feeling awkward about how to behave around his poorly mother.However, his wife Moira Barton (Natalie J. Robb) convinces him to go to the event to be there for Faith. At the Woolpack, there's a slight awkwardness as Faith begins her speech to guests but everyone relaxes when she starts singing her favourite karaoke song.Just as the part is in full swing, Faith suddenly collapses at the bar and leaves everyone concerned.Will this be the moment Cain goes to her rescue and holds her while they wait for an ambulance to arrive?Could she tragically die in her son's arms before the medics arrive?  DON'T MISS...Emmerdale theory: Marlon's estranged mother makes soap debut [EXCLUSIVE]Lisa Riley age: How old is Emmerdale's Mandy Dingle star? [EXPLAINER]Emmerdale theory: Manpreet Sharma to frame Naomi for Charles' death [UPDATE] Will Cain tell her he loves her and forgives her before she takes her final breath?Cain star Jeff opened up to Express.co.uk and other media about losing his soap mother in upcoming scenes.He revealed: "I'm personally saddened at losing the brilliant Sally Dexter, but it will give us some great stories going forward, so I look forward to that."Jeff also told ITV viewers during a recent appearance on Lorraine that Sally was a "great human being" and he was "sad we're losing her."